    "last_activity_date" : 1742872350,
    "last_edit_date" : 1742872350,
    "creation_date" : 1349440478,
    "answer_id" : 12746379,
    "question_id" : 2059431,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Configuring and running the maven-eclipse plugin, (for example from the command line <code>mvn eclipse:eclipse</code> )</p>\n<pre><code>  &lt;build&gt;\n    &lt;plugins&gt;\n      &lt;plugin&gt;\n        &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;\n        &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-eclipse-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n        &lt;configuration&gt;\n          &lt;downloadSources&gt;true&lt;/downloadSources&gt;\n          &lt;downloadJavadocs&gt;true&lt;/downloadJavadocs&gt;\n        &lt;/configuration&gt;\n      &lt;/plugin&gt;\n    &lt;/plugins&gt;\n  &lt;/build&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 156161,
      "reputation" : 2199,
      "user_id" : 373287,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/678e99bce763ad7625cd16c5cb0efd0c?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "eeezyy",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/373287/eeezyy"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1364235264,
    "creation_date" : 1364235264,
    "answer_id" : 15621847,
    "question_id" : 2059431,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I have also used the eclipse plugin to get the project into the eclipse workspace.\nSince I've worked on a different project I saw that it is possible to work with eclipse but without the maven-eclipse-plugin. That makes it easier to use with different environments and enables the easy use of maven over eclipse. And that without changing the pom.xml-file.</p>\n\n<p>So, I recommend the approach of Gabriel Ramirez.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2680559,
      "reputation" : 5155,
      "user_id" : 2317829,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 76,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e45dd81d0238dfb6d9a9adcf3dcf12f7?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "eebbesen",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2317829/eebbesen"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1409943584,
    "last_edit_date" : 1495540507,
    "creation_date" : 1389280105,
    "answer_id" : 21023889,
    "question_id" : 2059431,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Based on watching the Maven console in Eclipse (Kepler), sources will be automatically downloaded for a Maven dependency if you attempt to open a class from said Maven dependency  in the editor for which you do not have the sources downloaded already.  This is handy when you don't want to grab source for all of your dependencies, but you don't know which ones you want ahead of time (and you're using Eclipse).</p>\n\n<p>I ended up using <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/12498717/2317829\">@GabrielRamierez's approach</a>, but will employ <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/2059802/2317829\">@PascalThivent's approach</a> going forward. </p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 1502229,
        "reputation" : 3121,
        "user_id" : 1406510,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 64,
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1672f08b7ed6e1bbe72e70c690f49198?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "nanosoft",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1406510/nanosoft"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1436169342,
      "post_id" : 24503168,
      "comment_id" : 50478771,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Instead of downloading sources for all dependencies, is it possible to download just for some dependencies by specifying it in pom along with dependency itself, may b via some inner tag in dependency tag or something similar?"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 415813,
      "reputation" : 3300,
      "user_id" : 790839,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/ReU0T.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Anver Sadhat",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/790839/anver-sadhat"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 19,
    "last_activity_date" : 1404193396,
    "creation_date" : 1404193396,
    "answer_id" : 24503168,
    "question_id" : 2059431,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>To download some <strong>specific source or javadoc</strong> we need to include the GroupIds - Its a comma separated value as shown below</p>\n\n<pre><code>mvn dependency:sources -DincludeGroupIds=com.jcraft,org.testng -Dclassifier=sources\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Note that the classifier are not comma separated, to download the javadoc we need to run the above command one more time with the classifier as javadoc</p>\n\n<pre><code>mvn dependency:sources -DincludeGroupIds=com.jcraft,org.testng -Dclassifier=javadoc\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 47283,
        "reputation" : 723399,
        "user_id" : 139985,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 69,
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/147c5a9cc1feec049c50da791ac7d144?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "Stephen C",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/139985/stephen-c"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 2,
      "creation_date" : 1463811299,
      "post_id" : 25681447,
      "comment_id" : 62233439,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Answers a different question.  This question is about downloading source JARs not generating them."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2019551,
      "reputation" : 450,
      "user_id" : 1806062,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/siPW1.jpg?s=256",
