    "question_id" : 2059431,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you're using Eclipse, I would recommend downloading both the source <strong>and</strong> the Javadocs of third-party libraries.</p>\n<p>Right click on project and download both as per the screenshot below.</p>\n<p>Downloading Javadocs means that typically you can get contextual help for methods from third-party libraries, with useful description of parameters, etc. This is essential if you don't know the library well. In some cases I have found that Javadocs are available when the source isn't.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/2zmL0.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/2zmL0.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n"
